name: Katie Kramer
about:
What can I say about myself? There's not much that doesn't feel like it's ever-changing.

I am a daughter, sister, doting auntie, friend, and willing companion to those in my life. I've learned that independence can be as freeing as it is hazardous to one's personality. The more I age, the more I realize personal connections come in many forms, in many ways, and have staying power past what you may think possible.

I can be known to work too much (and care too much about it), I don't play quite as hard as I'd like to at other times, and I don't ever get enough sleep! I am happy with my life, friends, family, and myself. I've learned through experience that the worst thing a person can say to me is that I "work too hard and play too hard". (What is "too hard" anyways?!) It probably doesn't need to be said that the person who said that is no longer in my life. I try to balance the stressful, non-stop 24/7 immediacy of my work life with positive people, activities, and thoughts. With all that said, I like competition, yet exhibit a lack of drama. I have my days where I positively do not want to be thought of as the "intelligent one"... but I rock it anyways. :)

Despite all that, the thought of being "content" = "constant change". I'm always up for something new!

Right now, "something new" is learning to row in Lake Union and signing up for a couple of open water swim competitions this summer. Add to that list a burlesque class...and you see there isn't much I won't at least try.

name: Dustin Langan
about: I worked as a translator and interpreter for the Coalition Provisional Authority in Baghdad from April 2003 to February 2004. During that time I was involved in mass grave excavation, land mine removal, de-Baathification interviews, document retrieval, human rights promotion and the provision of technical support to emerging Iraqi civil activists. Born in Honolulu in 1974, I speak English, Arabic, French, Wolof, Spanish and Catalan. I live in Barcelona, Spain.
